The paper deals with the problem of Bayesian structure learning, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also discusses graph theoretic restrictions on the super-structure, which is a concept related to graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with score-based Bayesian structure learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses computational complexity and hardness results, which are related to theoretical computer science and fall under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses treewidth and degree, which are concepts related to information theory and fall under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses improving a given network by means of at most k arc additions, arc deletions, or arc reversals, which is related to optimization and falls under the category of cs.SI (Systems and Control).
